                  , D. D. On the <rs id="t17730113-53-cd316" type="crimeDate">20th of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17730113-53-off314 t17730113-53-cd316"></join>, about the hour of seven in the night, and stealing two linen table cloths, value 2 s. one linen surplice, value 5 s. one silver-cup, value 3 l. one silver rummer, value 20 s. two silver salts, value 20 s. one silver snuffer stand, value 10 s. one pair of steel snuffers with silver bows, value 5 s. one silver salver, value 40 s. one silver cruet frame, value 20 s. one silver salt shovel, value 2 s. one pair of French plate candlesticks, value 5 s. and four yards of silk, value 5 s. the property<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177301130040"></xptr> of the said Lewis; two linen sheets, value 4 s. and one stuff gown, value 5 s. the property of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17730113-53-victim595" type="victimName">
